<taxonomicName LSID="A9AFC28D-6814-52BF-B29D-3DD7FA9D9E21" authority="L. A. Nilsson, Kongl. Svenska Vetenskap. - Akad. Handl. 24 (14): 61 - 62. 1892." authorityName="L. A. Nilsson, Kongl. Svenska Vetenskap. - Akad. Handl. 24 (14): 61 - 62. 1892." class="Liliopsida" family="Xyridaceae" genus="Xyris" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Xyris glaziowii" order="Poales" pageId="3" pageNumber="68" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="glaziowii">Xyris glaziowii L.A.Nilsson, Kongl. Svenska Vetenskap.-Akad. Handl. 24(14): 61-62. 1892.</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="68" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="68">
<typeStatus>Type</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="68">
<normalizedToken originalValue="“Brasilien”">
&quot;
<collectingCountry name="Brazil">Brasilien</collectingCountry>
&quot;
</normalizedToken>
, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="68">Glaziou 8004</emphasis>
(B†; 
<typeStatus>lectotype</typeStatus>
, 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="68">designated here</emphasis>
: P! [P00753734]; isolectotypes: NY! [NY00246945], BR [BR000000694356, scan!], P! [P00753735]).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="68">
= 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Xyridaceae" genus="Xyris" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Xyris augusto-coburgii" order="Poales" pageId="3" pageNumber="68" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="augusto-coburgii">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="68">Xyris augusto-coburgii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Szyszyl. ex G.Beck., Itin. Princ. S. Coburgii 2: 94. 1888.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="68">
This name is a synonym of 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Xyridaceae" genus="Xyris" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Xyris augusto-coburgii" order="Poales" pageId="3" pageNumber="68" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="augusto-coburgii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="68">Xyris augusto-coburgii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Szyszyl. ex G.Beck. Although cited in the protologue as deposited in B, the type material of 
<taxonomicName genus="X." lsidName="X. glaziowii" pageId="3" pageNumber="68" rank="species" species="glaziowii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="68">X. glaziowii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is no longer to be found there. Dr. Robert Vogt, curator of B, has confirmed that the type material of 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Xyridaceae" genus="Xyris" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Xyris glaziowii" order="Poales" pageId="3" pageNumber="68" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="glaziowii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="68">Xyris glaziowii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
probably disappeared as a result of World War II damage to the B herbarium. Duplicates of 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="68">Glaziou 8004</emphasis>
at P, BR, NY, and a photograph at F were therefore examined with a view to selection of a 
<typeStatus>lectotype</typeStatus>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Smith, LB" editor="Hoehne, FC" journalOrPublisher="Sao Paulo, fasc. 12, v. 9, n. 2" pageId="10" pageNumber="75" pagination="1 - 214" refId="B16" refString="Smith, LB, Downs, RJ, 1968. Xyridaceae. In: Hoehne, FC, Teixeira, AR, Eds., Flora Brasilica. Sao Paulo, fasc. 12, v. 9, n. 2: 1 - 214" title="Xyridaceae." volumeTitle="Flora Brasilica." year="1968">Smith and Downs (1968)</bibRefCitation>
indicated material deposited at P as the type. However, there are two sheets of 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="68">Glaziou 
<quantity metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.033016" unit="in" value="8004.0">8004 in</quantity>
</emphasis>
this herbarium, and the sheet numbered P00753734 was chosen and designated here as the 
<typeStatus>lectotype</typeStatus>
, because of its more complete label data, stating that the material is from 
<collectingRegion country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo">
<normalizedToken originalValue="São">Sao</normalizedToken>
Paulo
</collectingRegion>
, Fazenda da Bocaina, near Cascatinha do rio Mambucabo, collected on 
<date value="1876-02-11">February 11, 1876</date>
. The isolectotypes are: P00753735, NY00246945 and BR000000694356, which although from the same collection (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="68">Glaziou 8004</emphasis>
), have incomplete label information. The BR sheet indicates that it originated from 
<collectingRegion country="Brazil" name="Rio de Janeiro">Rio de Janeiro</collectingRegion>
, while the label data of the NY sheet indicates its origin as 
<collectingRegion country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo">
<normalizedToken originalValue="São">Sao</normalizedToken>
Paulo
</collectingRegion>
, Bocaina, as in the 
<typeStatus>lectotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
